CatDescriptText: Cutline of related image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, January 6, 1962, pg. A14, reads: "YOUTHFUL SORORITY - Phi Delta Iota, a sorority composed of young women, held a gay New Year's party Dec. 29, at Sportsmen's Post 913 in Homewood. Many teen-agers from the tri-state area were on hand to help the group celebrate.  Left to right, seated: Felicia Tatum, Vonda Carza, Sylvia Barksdale, Maxine Lawrence and Barbara Miller.  Standing: Marlene Jefferies, Judy Berry, Phyllis Clark, LaDora Bell, Jolene Green, Joyce Smith, Mrs. Loretta Lawson, Pat Roberts, Carole Stone and Evelyn Allen. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Group portrait of fifteen women from Phi Delta Iota sorority wearing ribbons, seated left to right: Felicia Tatum, Vonda Carza, Sylvia Barksdale, Maxine Lawrence, and Barbara Miller; standing: Marlene Jefferies, Judy Berry, Phyllis Clark, LaDora Bell, Jolene Green, Joyce Smith, Loretta Lawson, Pat Roberts, Carole Stone, and Evelyn Allen, posed in front of Christmas tree for party in VFW sportsmens post 913
